article.headline: San Francisco defeats Cleveland St. 91-82
article.story: SAN FRANCISCO -- In a Nov. 13 story about a college basketball game between the San Francisco Dons and the Cleveland State Vikings, The Associated Press misidentified the Dons' coach. He's Rex Walters not Rex Chapman. A corrected version of the story is below: San Francisco defeats Cleveland St. 91-82 Mark Tollefsen scores 18 for San Francisco in 91-82 win over Cleveland St. SAN FRANCISCO -- Mark Tollefsen had 18 points for San Francisco in its win over Cleveland State Wednesday night 91-82. The game was closely played throughout as neither team took a double-digit lead until the closing minutes. San Francisco trailed 67-64 with 6:53 remaining in the second half. The Dons used a 27-8 run late in the second half to turn a nine point deficit into a ten point lead. Five players scored in double-figures for the Dons (2-0) including 17 off the bench for Tim Derksen. Cole Dickerson had the game's lone double-double with 14 points and 13 rebounds. Sebastian Douglas led the Vikings (1-1) in scoring with 15. The Dons made 50 percent from the beyond the arc, going 8-of-16, a staple for the Rex Walters led program that was top 5 nationally last year in 3-point field goal percentage.
